Delhi Capitals named Axar Patel as its captain for the IPL 2025 season on Friday.

Axar, with Delhi Capitals since 2019, was its top retention for Rs 16.50 crore ahead of the 2024 mega auction. Though lacking extensive captaincy experience, he was Indiaâ€™s T20I vice-captain in January 2025. He has led Gujarat in 23 matches, including the Syed Mushtaq Ali and Vijay Hazare Trophies.

Axar captained DC once last season, losing a match to RCB. He enters IPL 2025 after a key role in Indiaâ€™s Champions Trophy win, excelling with both bat and ball.

The team will kick off its campaign against the Lucknow Super Giants in Visakhapatnam on March 24.
